h1. {color:#6366f1}Prompt2Test{color} — CAP Design Improvements

{tip:title=High Availability, Consistency & Partition Tolerance}
Architectural enhancements across 4 tiers to make the platform production-ready. From quick wins to full multi-region active-active.
{tip}

----

{toc:minLevel=2|maxLevel=3}

----

h2. CAP Theorem Primer

{section}
{column:width=33%}
{panel:title=C — Consistency|borderColor=#2563eb|bgColor=#eff6ff}
Every read returns the most recent write. All nodes see the same data at the same time.

*Used by:* Aurora (single writer), DynamoDB strong reads
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=33%}
{panel:title=A — Availability|borderColor=#16a34a|bgColor=#f0fdf4}
Every request receives a response. System never refuses a request.

*Used by:* DynamoDB, CloudFront, Lambda
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=33%}
{panel:title=P — Partition Tolerance|borderColor=#ea580c|bgColor=#fff7ed}
System operates despite network partitions between nodes or regions.

*Used by:* DynamoDB Global Tables, Aurora Global DB
{panel}
{column}
{section}

----

h2. Current State Assessment

|| Component || Setup || Consistency || Availability || Partition Tolerant || Gap ||
| *Aurora Serverless v2* | Single region, auto-pause | {status:colour=Green|title=Strong} | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Partial} | {status:colour=Red|title=No} | 30s cold start on resume |
| *DynamoDB* | Single region, eventual reads | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Eventual} | {status:colour=Green|title=High} | {status:colour=Red|title=No} | May serve stale config |
| *ECS Fargate* | On-demand, single AZ | N/A | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Partial} | {status:colour=Red|title=No} | Tasks may land in 1 AZ |
| *Cognito* | Single region | {status:colour=Green|title=Strong} | {status:colour=Green|title=High} | {status:colour=Red|title=No} | Region failure = no login |
| *Bedrock AgentCore* | us-east-1 only | N/A | {status:colour=Green|title=High} | {status:colour=Red|title=No} | No cross-region fallback |
| *Lambda* | Single region | N/A | {status:colour=Green|title=High} | {status:colour=Red|title=No} | Cold starts under burst |
| *CloudFront + Amplify* | Global CDN | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Eventual} | {status:colour=Green|title=High} | {status:colour=Green|title=Yes} | Only PT component |

{warning:title=Critical Finding}
The platform is *single-region (us-east-1)*. If that region has an outage, everything is down. CloudFront is the only partition-tolerant component.
{warning}

----

h2. Recommended CAP Strategy

|| Data / Operation || Strategy || Rationale ||
| Service config reads (DynamoDB) | {status:colour=Blue|title=CP — Strong} | Agent MUST see latest URLs. Stale config = wrong environment. |
| Test case writes (Aurora) | {status:colour=Blue|title=CP — Strong} | Cannot lose results. PASS/FAIL must be durable. |
| Test case reads / listing | {status:colour=Green|title=AP — Eventual OK} | Inventory can lag 1-2s. User won't notice. |
| Browser sessions (ECS) | {status:colour=Green|title=AP — Availability} | Better to start degraded than refuse. |
| Authentication (Cognito) | {status:colour=Blue|title=CP — Strong} | Tokens must be valid. No stale credentials. |
| AI Agent responses (Bedrock) | {status:colour=Green|title=AP — Availability} | Fall back to simpler model if unavailable. |
| Run records (Aurora) | {status:colour=Blue|title=CP — Strong} | Source of truth. Must not be lost. |

----

h2. Tier 1 — Quick Wins (1-2 days)

|| # || Enhancement || Impact || Cost ||
| 1.1 | *DynamoDB: Strong Consistent Reads* — add {{ConsistentRead: true}} to all config queries | Eliminates stale config | +$0.50/mo |
| 1.2 | *Aurora: Verify Multi-AZ* — ensure writer + reader in different AZs | Survives AZ failure | +$30/mo |
| 1.3 | *ECS: Multi-AZ Task Placement* — spread tasks across 2+ AZs | Browser sessions survive AZ loss | $0 |
| 1.4 | *Lambda: Reserved Concurrency* — set minimum for reader/writer | Avoid cold starts under load | $0-15/mo |
| 1.5 | *CloudWatch Alarms + SNS* — Aurora errors, Lambda errors, ECS failures | Know before users complain | +$1/mo |

----

h2. Tier 2 — Production Hardening (1-2 weeks)

|| # || Enhancement || Impact || Cost ||
| 2.1 | *API Gateway in front of Lambda* — rate limiting, throttling, validation | Prevents overload | +$3/mo |
| 2.2 | *Dead Letter Queues* — SQS DLQ for Lambda failures | Never lose test results | +$0.40/mo |
| 2.3 | *WAF on CloudFront* — rate limiting, bot protection | DDoS protection | +$5/mo |
| 2.4 | *Secrets Manager Auto-Rotation* — rotate Aurora credentials every 30 days | Security compliance | +$0.40/mo |
| 2.5 | *Aurora Auto-Pause Retry* — exponential backoff + CloudWatch canary during business hours | Eliminates #1 user error | +$3/mo |
| 2.6 | *S3 Cross-Region Replication* — replicate build artifacts to us-west-2 | CI/CD survives region failure | ~$0.02/GB |

----

h2. Tier 3 — Multi-Region (2-4 weeks)

|| # || Enhancement || Impact || Cost ||
| 3.1 | *DynamoDB Global Tables* — replicate config to us-west-2 | Config survives region failure | 1.5x writes |
| 3.2 | *Aurora Global Database* — read replica in us-west-2, ~1s replication | Data survives region failure | +$50/mo |
| 3.3 | *ECS Cluster in us-west-2* — Fargate tasks in both regions | Browser tests run anywhere | On-demand |
| 3.4 | *Route 53 DNS Failover* — auto-route to healthy region | Automatic region failover | +$1/mo |
| 3.5 | *Cognito Backup* — long-lived JWT tokens + backup User Pool | Auth survives region failure | 1 day effort |
| 3.6 | *Bedrock Cross-Region Fallback* — retry against us-west-2 on 429/5xx | AI survives region issues | $0 |

----

h2. Tier 4 — Active-Active (1-2 months)

|| # || Enhancement || Impact || Cost ||
| 4.1 | *AWS Global Accelerator* — anycast IPs, failover <30s | Instant failover | +$18/mo |
| 4.2 | *Multi-Region CI/CD* — parallel deploy to both regions | Consistent versions | Pipeline cost |
| 4.3 | *Multi-Account Strategy* — separate AWS accounts per env | Blast radius isolation | Org setup |
| 4.4 | *Chaos Engineering* — AWS Fault Injection Simulator monthly | Validates all improvements | ~$5/mo |

----

